<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have a heat on • heat is on, the</xh5><p> <i>have a heat on</i>—(U.S. sl.) be alcohol or drug intoxicated: A few years ago this dump was full of dope. Every other man you met <u>had a heat on</u>.</p><p><i>heat is on, the—</i>1. said when strong pressure is brought to bear: She says now that <u>the heat is on</u>, the people can depend on the union to stand up strong at the negotiation table. 2. <i>(U.S. coll.)</i> said when police activities or investigations are at their peak: <u>The heat is on</u> in Baltimore. The drug war is being lost ... and a desperate mayor wants the crime rates down before the election.</p> </entry>
